Scanner class
==========================================================
The Scanner Class in java is part of the java.util.package and commonly used to take INPUT from the user.

import.java.util.scanner

Syntax : Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

1) nextInt(): Reads integer values.
2) nextFloat(): Reads float value.
3) nextLine(): Reads string value until newline character ('\n') is encountered.
4) next(): Reads string value until space or newline character is encountered.
5) nextDouble(): Reads double value.
6) nextBoolean(): Reads boolean value.

